properties.Name: Enbridge Line 78 (former 6B)
properties.EPA: Line 78 is a  373 mile long pipeline carrying light, medium and heavy crudes. Let's be clear, it's really two lines grouped together: a 36-inch diameter pipe carrying 570,000 barrels per day from Flanagan Terminal to Griffith Terminal, and a 30-inch diameter pipe carrying 500,000 barrels per day from Griffith Terminal to Sarnia.
